==English==

===Adjective===

# personal attribute, often pejorative, - averse to cold weather (water, etc.), more susceptible to feeling it than normal.

===Examples / Explanation===
"No, tha'd drop down stiff, as dead as a door-knob, wi' thy nesh sides." 
''Sons and Lovers.'' D.H. Lawrence

A person averse to going out in cold weather, someone who puts on warm clothing at the slightest hint of a coolish breeze, someone who is averse to going swimming because the water is less than ideally warm.

The sensation of feeling the cold more acutely than normal.

===Locality===
This word seems to be specific to an area around Stafford and Stoke-on-Trent, in the North West Midlands of England also in the East Midlands. 

(confirmed around Tideswell/Buxton, Derbyshire)